If it is determined that a cross-metering situation exists. The tenants involved will be rendered corrected bills to cover such period of time as the statute of limitations allows. If a tenant has been underbilled, the tenant shall be allowed to make
      payment of the amount underbilled in equal monthly installments for as many months as the corrected bill covers, but for not more than ten (10) months, the entire amount underbilled being due upon termination of tenancy. If a tenant has been overbilled
      and is due a credit, the tenant may request a cash refund, otherwise such credit shall be posted to the tenant’s account;
